re, in which Japan’s imperial subjects were mobilized to regularly perform highly orchestrated civil air defense drills throughout the country. The war years in Japan are often portrayed as a landscape of privation and suppression under the censorship of the war machine. But alongside the horrors, pleasure, desire, wonder, creativity, and humor were all still abundantly present in a period before air raids went from being a fearful specter to a deadly reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAir defensesxSocial aspectszJapan. 0aAir defenses-Social aspects-Japan. 0aJapan-Civilization-1926-1945. 0aJapan-Social life and customs-1912-1945. 0aMilitarizationzJapanxHistoryy20th century. 0aMilitarization-Japan-History-20th century. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945xSocial aspectszJapan. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945-Social aspects-Japan. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aboku, civil air defense, japan, visual culture, bombs, gas masks, airplanes, futuristic weapons, fashion, magazines, promotional giveaways, war, empire, drills, propaganda, government posters, advertising, cartoons, postcards, newsreels, film, art, nonfiction, history, politics, social mobilization, play, desire, pleasure, humor, creativity, aesthetics, consumption, gender, aerial bombardment.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076650940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226816456423